  "text": "The study was divided into 4 periods, during which time water input and output and metabolizable energy intake were determined: before pregnancy for 14 days, during pregnancy for 21 days starting 7-10 days after the onset of pregnancy, during the first 7 days of a 21-day lactation (fecal and urine output of the offspring were negligible the first 7 days- [CITATION_1] , and postweaning for 7 days. Gestation was taken as the 40 days prior to parturition. Details on simultaneous measurement of energy intake on these same females have been presented previously [CITATION_2] ; included in that report is the growth rate of the offspring.",
